  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the potatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 395&deg;F/ Gas 6.</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins&nbsp;on) into small bite-sized pieces.</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> from the stalks.</p>\r\n<p>Crush the <strong>garlic</strong> (skins on) with the back of a knife.</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong>, <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up.</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 30 min or until the potatoes are golden and crispy.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the steaks</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, trim the fat from the <strong>rump steaks.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover the <strong>steaks</strong> in<strong> cling film</strong> and bash them with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flat and approx. half a cm in thickness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: this will make the steaks really tender!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670...step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the ingredients for breading</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add a handful of&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong>&nbsp;to a plate with a generous pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Crack the&nbsp;<strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork.</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>panko breadcrumbs&nbsp;</strong>to a plate with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong>.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1670.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Bread the steaks</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat the <strong>steaks</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then dip into the <strong>beaten egg</strong> and press it into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to coat everything evenly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: make sure the steaks are fully coated in the breadcrumbs!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
